metadata.name: Melting Romance
metadata.description:
People shape their identities by internalizing the social facts of the society. Social identities that develop within the framework of gender, language, religion and ethnicity from the moment we have born becomes like the first clothes we wear and never take off. People mask their real essence and impose a different definition on themselves to gain a place in the society.

As the main element of the collection, here we have the person unidentified. Now the real question is; who is this?
